  "title": "Project Manager (Commercial/A&A)",
  "description": "<p>For this position, we envisage an energetic,dynamic and capable person with relevant experience in the built environment sector. This is for interior renovations as well as addition and alteration (A&A) works. The main works area focus are commercial buildings, offices, as well as the industrial, aviation and transport infrastructure.</p><p>The successful candidate will report to the Project Director / Managing Director, collaborate with department HODs and team members of each project team.</p><p>Key responsibilities</p><ul><li>Managing overall site works with planned periodic updates and reports (internally and externally), including liaison with tenant owners, own employer representatives, MCSTs and FM counterparts.</li><li>Be the point of contact and liaison for scheduling / planning / execution of work for our workers and sub-contractors</li><li>Resolve site issues, challenges and conflicts where necessary</li><li>Ensure smooth and successful delivery of any tasked project</li><li>Plan overall master and micro project schedules, in Gantt chart formats, execute as tasked</li><li>End-to-end follow ups on contract and variations till closure of accounts.</li><li>Assist the team in bids with PM proposals; planning, VE, health and safety, risk assessments etc</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
